    <title>RADSerial</title>
    <briefdescription>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para><computeroutput><ref refid="namespaceRADSerial" kindref="compound">RADSerial</ref></computeroutput> provides Linux serial port support through <computeroutput><ref refid="classRADSerial_1_1RADSerialPort" kindref="compound">RADSerial::RADSerialPort</ref></computeroutput>. It uses <computeroutput><ref refid="classRADCore_1_1RADIODevice" kindref="compound">RADCore::RADIODevice</ref></computeroutput> and posts read availability through <computeroutput><ref refid="classRADCore_1_1EventLoop" kindref="compound">RADCore::EventLoop</ref></computeroutput>.</para>
<para>Core features:</para>
<para><itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>Baud rate, data bits, parity, stop bits, and flow control configuration.</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Async <computeroutput>readyRead</computeroutput> delivery.</para>
</listitem><listitem><para><computeroutput>RADIODevice</computeroutput> read/write compatibility.</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Basic <computeroutput>/dev</computeroutput> serial port discovery. </para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
    </detaileddescription>
    <location file="docs/public/radserial.md"/>
  </compounddef>
</doxygen>
